{"_id":"K0ygnJNiFu1khvSw","name":"Vehicles - Items, Modifications, & Equipment","content":"<p>All adventurers need gear to help them complete their quests, and scavengers in Odium are no exception. While most of the gear commonly found at trading posts and general stores will also be available in The Sundered Lands, there are some other items and equipment common to life in the wastes that may not be found elsewhere - chief among them are components and modifications to customize your ride.</p>\n<h3><strong>Components and Parts</strong></h3>\n<p>Buying, trading, bartering for, begging for, and otherwise acquiring vehicle components and parts is a daily affair in the lives of scavengers. These components are about the only reliable import into Bastion; those in the Upper Decks sponsoring a scavenger guild use their power and connections to guarantee these crucial items find their way into Bastion by way of supply airships. Keeping their scavengers happy is the most important thing to a sponsor or guild leader - scavengers can’t make them any money otherwise.</p>\n<p>The most ideal way to purchase components is to purchase them new. When possible, scavengers prefer to have brand new components flown in by airship or constructed on-site by the most skilled black thumbs available. This gets pricey, but new components will last longer and are easier to work on - nothing but the best will do for a guild’s MVPs. Used components are much more readily available and thus can be acquired easily and for less money, but obviously won’t last as long.</p>\n<p>The tables below all break down the base costs and modifiers to components based on a number of parameters. All prices below are given for components in the Auto classification and of the Ground type, with the Classification Modifiers table showing how to modify the component price for components in another vehicle classification and type. The exception to this rule is the Body components, for which prices are given for each classification and type specifically with no need for price modification.</p>\n<p>Swapping out or installing a component part requires a Craft skill check with a DC of 15 + the Component’s main stat. The install time for components is always two 8-hour days, with each day calling for the Craft skill check. Failure simply means the time is lost, but the installer can try again the following day without penalty and without losing any material.</p>\n<h3><strong>Component Base Costs and Descriptions</strong></h3>\n<p>This section will spell out the most basic costs of components of a given type for the component’s Horsepower, Power Transfer, Reactivity, or Brakes value as given on the table below. Most follow a pattern, which extends past the value given on the table for even higher-quality components (where applicable), though these components are exceedingly rare at the best of times, let alone in Bastion, and their purchase and availability should be treated with great care by a Game Master.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>@Compendium[tsl-content.tsl-rules.5PRsKcEsizUcwGyz]{Body Descriptions}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[tsl-content.tsl-rules.qiQLRCvKrpBCk1F1]{Engine Descriptions}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[tsl-content.tsl-rules.8MAFpYXYpSpXieVu]{Transmission Descriptions}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[tsl-content.tsl-rules.v9CTejiMLBDcFP3p]{Suspension Descriptions}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[tsl-content.tsl-rules.IK7327TO436bD4EG]{Chassis Descriptions}</li>\n</ol>\n<table style=\"width:74.3553%;height:527px\" border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:100%;height:17px\" colspan=\"6\">Ground Body Style Costs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"text-align:center;height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:24.7104%;height:17px\">Style</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.305%;height:17px\">Crew Capacity</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:11.9691%;height:17px\">Doors</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:12.7413%;height:17px\">Top</td>\n<td style=\"te